{"word":"H1687 - דְּבִיר - dᵉbîyr - deb-eer' - Oracle","slug":"H1687","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דְּבִיר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dᵉbîyr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>deb-eer'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Oracle"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>דּבר דּביר</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>debı̂yr debir</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>deb-eer'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p><ol><li>the holy of holies, the innermost room of the temple or tabernacle<ol type='a'><li>hindmost chamber, innermost room of the temple of Solomon, most holy place, holy of holies</li></ol><li>(TWOT) oracle</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H1696\">H1696</a> (apparently in the sense of oracle) <p />TWOT entry: <a class=\"T\" href=\"S:0399 - dabar\">399g</a> <p />Part(s) of speech: Noun Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1682\">H1682</a>, <a href=\"#/H1683\">H1683</a>, <a href=\"#/H1688\">H1688</a>, <a href=\"#/H1696\">H1696</a>, <a href=\"#/H1697\">H1697</a>, <a href=\"#/H1698\">H1698</a>, <a href=\"#/H1699\">H1699</a>, <a href=\"#/H1700\">H1700</a>, <a href=\"#/H1702\">H1702</a>, <a href=\"#/H1703\">H1703</a>, <a href=\"#/H1704\">H1704</a>, <a href=\"#/H1705\">H1705</a>, <a href=\"#/H4057\">H4057</a>"}]}